The paper deals with independent sets in graphs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The concepts of maximum independent sets, critical independent sets, and their intersections and unions are also relevant to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also presents new characterizations of Koenig-Egervary graphs, which are a class of graphs with important applications in network flow algorithms, making cs.NA a likely sub-category as well. Finally, the paper involves some geometric considerations, which could potentially place it in the cs.CG sub-category.
